SENTENCE and not too long ago ,  a new approach was used to find out if the botai people were keeping horses .
SENTENCE soil samples from these pens or corrals show ten times the concentration of phosphorus .
SENTENCE yes .
SENTENCE phosphorus is a very significant indicator that horses ,  large numbers of horses were being kept in the settlements .
SENTENCE you see ,  horse manure ,  horse waste is rich in phosphorus and also nitrogen compared to normal soil .
SENTENCE but nitrogen is an unstable element .
SENTENCE it can be washed out when it rains or it can be released to the atmosphere ,  whereas phosphorus combines with calcium and iron ,  and can be preserved in the soil for thousands of years .
SENTENCE the soil from the botai settlement sites was found to have high concentrations of phosphorus and low nitrogen concentrations ,  which is important since it suggests that what we've got is really old ,  not something added to the soil more recently .
SENTENCE wait .
SENTENCE so if horses have been there recently ,  there'd still be lots of nitrogen in the soil .
